                <p>The  Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation in Collaboration with the Nigerian Institution of Water Engineers, Nigerian Society of Engineers,  Nigerian Bottling Company and other major Stakeholders celebrates World Water Day on 22nd March,2023.
                </p>
                <p>  The  2023 World Water Day Celebration is all about  accelerating Change to Solve the water and Sanitation Crisis all over the world.  The change  that encourages people to take action in their lives to Change  how the use, Consume and Manage Water.  The  SA to the governor honorable  Tanana Biaduo, the managing Director Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation Engr Emeka Ugoanyanwu, the Chairman Nigerian Institution of Water Engineers Engr Dr Miike Nwachukwu and other Stakeholders from Wash Community troop out in mass to create awareness and advocate for safe water because water is life and  Sanitation is dignity. </p>
                <p> In the process  of the 2023 World Water Day Celebration the guest  Lecturer Engr Dr Okore Okoroafor recieved  an award for immense Contribution towards the development of Engineering in Nigeria.</p>
                <p> Conclusively, the  UN, Nigerian  Institution of water Engineers Imo State Chapter in Collaboration with Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation and the Nigerian Society of Engineers Owerri branch presented Certificate  Of participation for  2023 World Water Day Celebration to the following.
                </p>
                  <p>  </p>
                 <p><strong> (1)Hon  Tanana  Biaduo          : SA to the governor </strong></p>
                   <p><strong> (2) Engr Emeka Ugoanyawu    : MD/CEO  ISWSC</strong></p>
                   <p><strong>(4)Engr Dr Mike Nwachukwu   :Chairman  NIWE</strong></p>
                   <p><strong>(5)Engr  Dr Okore O Okoroafor  : FUTO</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>(6)Uchechi Deborah  Uchenna   :Wash Ambassador</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>(7)DE Living  Table  Water</strong></p>
                            <p><strong>(8)Saint _ Lewis Table  Water</strong></p>
                                <p><strong> (9)Frandi Table Water</strong></p>
                                    <p><strong>  (10)Josh -  Jay Table  Water</strong></p>
                                        <p><strong>  (11)Imo Government Girls Sec Sch</strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>  (12)ATWAP,  Imo State Chapter</strong></p>
                                                <p><strong> (13)Innovation Labs Academy</strong></p>
                                                    <p><strong> (14)Christine Science School Owerri</strong></p>
                                                        <p><strong> (15)Tochex Table Water</strong></p>
                                                            <p><strong> (16)Nigerian Society of Egineers</strong></p>
                                                                <p><strong> (17)2023 World Water Day Rapporteur</strong></p>
                <p> Let us embrace this powerful advocacy: Accelerating Change to Solve the water and Sanitation Crisis by changing the way we use, Consume and Manage water. Remember water is life and Sanitation is dignity.
                    </p>
